@mkaminski1988 Here's the quote from the KIP related to this:

> From a behavior perspective on the server (broker) side, when the expired-connection-kill feature is enabled with a positive value the broker will communicate a session time via SASL_AUTHENTICATE and will close a connection when the connection is used past the expiration time and the specific API request is not directly related to re-authentication (SaslHandshakeRequest and SaslAuthenticateRequest).  In other words, if a connection sits idle, it will not be closed â€“ something unrelated to re-authentication must traverse the connection before a disconnect will occur.

Does that clarify it?

